procedures.name: Blood Draw
procedures.label: Venipuncture
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), and clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation).

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of urine for various tests including urine drug screen, urinalysis, pregnancy tests, and 24-hour collection for copper and molybdenum measurement.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples for the measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to monitor heart rate and intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc).

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vitals
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full or symptom-driven physical examination, including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Medical History Collection
procedures.label: History Taking
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, Wilson disease history, demographics, and prior treatments.

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Ongoing monitoring and collection of adverse event (AE) and serious adverse event (SAE) information.

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurement
procedures.label: Height/Weight/BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: IV Cannulation
procedures.description: Placement of an intravenous cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Urine/Serum Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine or serum pregnancy testing for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Alcohol Test
procedures.label: Alcohol Screening
procedures.description: Test to screen for alcohol use.

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: UDS
procedures.description: Screening of urine for presence of disallowed drugs.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: Completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula placed in a vein to allow for repeated blood sampling.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Laboratory instrument used to determine copper and molybdenum concentration in biological and dietary samples.

medicalDevices.name: Male Condom
medicalDevices.label: Condom
medicalDevices.description: Barrier contraception required for male participants.
